⦿ .spun — the five-fold spin of The Logistic Curve
node POP · POP · ⟦The Logistic Curve:POP:992429⟧

WHO   — The Logistic Curve — growth meets the ceiling · rN(1−N/K)
WHAT  — The S-curve: exponential at first, then bending to a plateau — the shape of a population filling its niche.
WHERE — POP · Population Dynamics  Framework inputs: ecology, epidemiology, population genetics; Asimov's Foundation; verified & cited  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0 · Life Science)
WHY   — Because real growth is bounded, and the logistic is how the bound bends the rise.
HOW   — By multiplying the growth rate by (1 − N/K), so the closer N gets to K, the slower it climbs.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  I am the S: I rise like Malthus, then remember the ceiling and level off. ('Carrying capacity' came later than I did.)

